# Add your .mp4 video files here

This folder is for source video files that will be automatically extracted into animations.

## Supported formats

- `.mp4` (H.264 video codec recommended)
- All files ending in `.mp4` will be processed during build

## Examples

```
videos/
├── animation1.mp4
├── animation2.mp4
└── my-video.mp4
```

After uploading videos to this folder and deploying, they will be automatically extracted to:
- `anims/animation1/images/`
- `anims/animation2/images/`
- `anims/my-video/images/`

## Access via API

Once extracted, access your animations using the `anim` parameter:
```
GET /?anim=animation1&minframe=1&maxframe=10
GET /?anim=animation2&amount=1
```

## Important Notes

- Video frame extraction happens during the build process only
- Large videos may take several minutes to process
- Each frame is resized to 64x40 pixels and extracted at 5 FPS
- Frame extraction is lossless (PNG format with full color preservation)
